FBIS4-26992 "drchi125_w_94002" FBIS-CHI-94-125 Daily Report 27 Jun 1994 HONG KONG & MACAO Hong Kong Mayor Repeats Jiang's Comments on Shenzhen, Hong Kong Mayor Repeats Jiang's Comments on Shenzhen, Hong Kong HK2906034894 Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE in Chinese 0651 GMT 27 Jun 94 HK2906034894 Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE Chinese BFN [Text] Shenzhen, 27 Jun (ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE)--A few days ago, at a conference of all the city's cadres at or above the departmental level, Shenzhen City Mayor Li Youwei conveyed Jiang Zemin's comments made on a visit to the city on six aspects of Shenzhen's relations with Hong Kong. They are: One, utilization: utilize Hong Kong to help develop the city; two, reliance: rely on Hong Kong in moving toward the international community; three, taking reference: learn to do things according to Hong Kong and international conventions; four, making ties: establishing ties with Hong Kong and branching out in the hinterland; five, making distinctions: distinguishing between Hong Kong and one country, two systems; and six, convergence: converging with Hong Kong for mutual benefits. Li Youwei said: As the "1997" Hong Kong's transition is drawing closer, Shenzhen will play an important role in ensuring a stable transition, smooth return, and long-term prosperity for Hong Kong Shenzhen is a socialist special economic zone, and at no time is it an extension or expansion of Hong Kong. We must be clear-headed and have a clear understanding of this.
